  "raw_block": "Visions in sleep —Job 33:15;Da 2:28.\nOften by imaginary —Job 20:8;Isa 29:8.\nExcess of business frequently leads to —Ec 5:3.\nGod’s will often revealed in —Nu 12:6;Job 33:15.\nFalse prophets\n  Pretended to. —Jer 23:25-28;29:8.\n  Not to be regarded in. —De 13:1-3;Jer 27:9.\n  Condemned for pretending to. —Jer 23:32.\nVanity of trusting to natural —Ec 5:7.\nThe ancients\n  Put great faith in. —Jdj 7:15.\n  Often perplexed by. —Ge 40:6;41:8;Job 7:14;Da 2:1;4:5.\n  Anxious to have, explained. —Ge 40:8;Da 2:3.\n  Consulting magicians on. —Ge 41:8;Da 2:2-4.\nGod the only interpreter of —Ge 40:8;41:16;Da 2:27-30;7:16.\nMentioned in scripture of\n  Abimelech. —Ge 20:3-7.\n  Jacob. —Ge 28:12;31:10.\n  Laban. —Ge 31:24.\n  Joseph. —Ge 37:5-9.\n  Pharaoh’s butler and baker. —Ge 40:5-19.\n  Pharaoh. —Ge 41:1-7.\n  Midianite. —Jdj 7:13-15.\n  Solomon. —1Ki 3:5-15.\n  Nebuchadnezzar. —Da 2:1,31;4:5,8.\n  Daniel. —Da 7:1-28.\n  Joseph. —Mt 1:20,21;2:13,19,20.\n  Wise men. —Mt 2:11,12.\n  Pilate’s wife. —Mt 27:19.\nIllustrativ",
